Compounds of the invention have been found to inhibit HIV- 1 replication in cells infected with AZT-resistant HΓV- 1 strains as well as cells infected with PFA-resistant HTV-1 strains. 
Particularly preferred compounds of the invention exhibit EC50 values of about 10 μM or less, and more preferably about 1 μM or less against AZT resistant HIV-1 strains (such as A018-post) and/ or Foscamet resistant HTV- 1 strains (such as LAI-E89K) in standard HIV plaque reduction assays.
